<TITLE> Serbian judge seriously wounded in bomb attack </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BELGRADE, March 21 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A judge in southeastern Serbia was severely injured on Friday when an explosive device went off while he was opening the gate to leave his home for court, his colleague said. President of the Knjazevac court Dragisa Cvejic sustained serious abdominal and leg injuries and was rushed to the city of Nis for surgery. "It is too early to reach conclusions about who did this. All we can confirm is that there have been some threats," judge Miodrag Radosavljevic told Reuters. He said the attack might be connected to the cases his colleague was working on, but did not elaborate. "Our job can always carry dangers. There are always some parties in a trial who are dissatisfied with a ruling," he said. Police sealed off the area were awaiting experts from Belgrade to investigate the atta
